The dedicated section on prayascittas for women in the Āṅgirasa Smṛti is **"Penance for Children, the Elderly, and Women"** (Ang_2,10.20–21, paragraphs p-a3104f through p-8ca8c6, chapter 1 of `unknown-angirasa-smrti-2bf9d1`). It prescribes:
- **Half penance** for women who sinned intentionally (Ang_2,10.20)
- **Quarter penance** for eunuchs, children, the elderly, and women collectively (Ang_2,10.21)

This appears in Chapter 10 ("The Account of Penance for Injury") of the second Aṅgiras text embedded within the single-chapter work.
